---
layout: base.njk
title_id: services
---

<style>

.offers-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  align-items: stretch;
  row-gap: 2vh;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .offers-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
}

.offer {
  background-color: var(--black);
  color: var(--white);

  margin: 2vh 2vw;
  padding: 2vh 2vw;

  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .offer {
    padding: 4vh 6vw;
  }
}

.offer-content {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  flex: 1;
  min-height: 0;

}

.offer-title::before {
  content: "❖";
  margin-right: 0.5em;
}

.offer-middle {
  margin-top: 2vh;
}

.offer-footer {
  margin-top: auto;
  padding-top: 2vh;
}

.offer p {
  margin: 0 0 1.2vh 0;
}

.offer ul,
.offer ol {
  margin: 0;
  padding-left: 1.2em;
}

.offer li {
  margin-bottom: 0.5vh;
}

.explain {
  margin-top: 2vh;
}

.explain p {
  margin-bottom: 2vh;
}

.cta {
  color: var(--white);
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 1.2rem;
}

.msg {
  margin-top: 2vh;
}

</style>

<main>
  <h1>{{ global[title_id] | t(lang) }}</h1>

<section class="offers-grid">

{% for offer in services.offers %}
  {% if not offer.hidden %}
    <div class="offer">

      <h3 class="offer-title">{{ offer.title | t(lang) }}</h3>

      <div class="offer-content">
        <p>{{ offer.description | t(lang) | safe }}</p>

        <div class="offer-middle">
          <p><strong>Optimal for:</strong></p>
          {% for element in offer.optimal_for %}
            <li>{{ element | t(lang) }}</li>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>

        <div class="offer-footer">
          <p>{{ offer.pricing | t(lang) | safe }}</p>

          <a class="cta" href="/{{ lang }}/services/{{ offer.link }}/">
            ▸ {{ global["learn_more"] | t(lang) }}
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

</section>

<p class="msg">EUR (&euro;), USD (&dollar;) and JPY (&yen;) are accepted.</p>

<div class="explain">
<h2>{{ services.explain.title | t(lang) }}</h2>

<h3>Pricing Classification</h3>

<p>
Pricing may vary depending on the Client’s tax jurisdiction and applicable classification.
Clients may provide valid tax residency or fiscal documentation for classification purposes.
Where such documentation is provided, the Operator may apply region-specific pricing as defined in the relevant offer.
</p>

<p><strong>1.</strong> The Client contacts Operator Kai stating their needs.</p>

<p><strong>2.</strong> The Operator prepares and provides a minimum viable proposal for the Client.</p>

<p><strong>3.</strong> Once agreed, the Operator sends the Contract for the Client to sign (wet or digital signatures accepted) which regulates the relationship and applicable terms, including pricing classification.</p>

<p><strong>4.</strong> The Operator sends the Project Blueprint for the Client to evaluate. If approved, the Client must sign it. The Project Blueprint defines Scope, Milestones, Installments, and Operational Notes.</p>

<p><strong>5.</strong> Pricing and scope are defined in the Project Blueprint. The Project Blueprint establishes the initial scope, milestones, and total cost. Any changes to scope after approval require a revised or extended Project Blueprint, which may adjust pricing accordingly.</p>

<p><strong>6.</strong> The commission is paid in installments defined by the Project Blueprint.</p>

<p><strong>7.</strong> The Operator provides proof of completion of each milestone.</p>

<p><strong>8.</strong> The Client pays the final remaining amount, and the Operator delivers the project.</p>

<p class="msg">
Standard international pricing applies by default. Clients incorporated in Japan are eligible for Japan localized pricing (JPY billing only). Eligibility is determined based on the company’s country of incorporation as verified via its Japanese Corporate Number (法人番号). 
<br>
Japan pricing is fixed in Japanese Yen (JPY) and is not derived from or adjusted according to foreign exchange rates.
</p>

</div>

</main>
